DOC.TE:
   Metal works of art are melted down and sold as raw material;
marble is recycled for other graves. The sculptures were stolen to
order, Filip speculated.

   As a comparison, Cote gave these numbers for four other years in
which $3-million-plus houses were sold in Newport Beach: 17 (1997);
13 (1998); 25 (1999); and 38 (2000).

   Hotel Kimal, 452 Domingo Atienza, San Pedro de Atacama;
telephone/fax 851-030, www.kimal.cl, is an attractive small place
outside town. Rates begin at $84 per night, double.

   Nepalese: Gurkha's Brasserie, 190-192 Chapel St., Prahran;
9510-3325. Spicy fare at this restaurant, which is run by two
Nepalese brothers.

   Turkish: Kilim Turkish Restaurant, 366 Victoria St., Richmond;
9428-5982. Tents, kilim-covered walls and exotic Middle Eastern
dishes.

DOC.LD:
   The six-night trip begins in Singapore, where travelers spend two
days visiting Thian Hock Keng, one of the oldest temples in the city;
the National Orchid Garden; Chinatown; and handicraft shops.

DOC.TE:
   Class extroverts Keegan McFadden and Kyle Key, both 9, ham it up
for the seniors, most of whom stare at them seriously. One man,
wearing Mardi Gras beads, sings along and a woman claps to the beat.

   "We all agreed, wouldn't it be a wonderful thing to do 'A Concert
for America 2002,' " Henry Moran, the committee's executive director,
told the Washington Post.
